		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2015"></a><br><code>sle2015/paper16</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2015</a> paper:</span><br><i>XMLText: from XML schema to xtext</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/PatrickNeubauer.html">Patrick Neubauer</a>, <a href="../profile/AlexanderBergmayr.html">Alexander Bergmayr</a>, <a href="../profile/TanjaMayerhofer.html">Tanja Mayerhofer</a>, <a href="../profile/JavierTroya.html">Javier Troya</a>, <a href="../profile/ManuelWimmer.html">Manuel Wimmer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2814251.2814267">10.1145/2814251.2814267</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a generative approach that derives Xtext language artifacts from XML Schemas.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It targets XML-Schema-based DSLs and upgrades them toward modern DSL/editor support.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> Xtext-based generation directly produces language workbench assets such as parsers and IDE support.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2d.html"><span class="tagL">T2D: Deployment</span></a><ul><li> It aims to make DSL tooling more portable/usable across environments by moving to the Xtext ecosystem.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
